Key Match Events: Leweling scored the winning goal for Germany in the 64th minute.
Rudiger (63'), Schlotterbeck (90+3'), Anton (90+3') received yellow cards for Germany.
Reijnders (30'), Wieffer (63'), Simons (90+3') received yellow cards for Netherlands.
Pre-Game Insights: Both teams are still unbeaten at the halfway stage in the UEFA Nations League.
Germany has recorded wins over Hungary and Bosnia-Herzegovina, while Netherlands drew with Hungary.
Germany is sitting top of the section and benefiting from home advantage.
Netherlands will be without Virgil van Dijk due to suspension.
Post-Match Reflections: Germany's win means they have moved onto seven points in the UEFA Nations League, the same tally they managed in the entire of the previous edition.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany's win will seriously threaten Netherlands' unbeaten run away from home in the Nations League.
Others: The retirement of Manuel Neuer gave Marc-Andre ter Stegen the chance to step up as Germany's number one, but he is now out for the season.
Germany's Jamal Musiala and Kai Havertz are also injured and will not be available for the match.
Netherlands are short on options at left-back due to injuries and will likely shift Micky van de Ven out there.
